reviews.text:
Seriously... go here! As someone who's lived in Korea for the last 2 years, this place was basically heaven when it comes to bottle selection, and the selection on tap was great too. Relaxed outdoor seating area. Friendly staff. 
Weeks after visiting, plagued by the memory of a delicious brew that I tried here but unable to remember the name, I emailed the address from the website and they responded within the day with the exact info I was looking for. The definition of doing it right from top to bottom.
A good place to chill over the weekend. There are a great variety of beer. Really love the seat outside and the ambience

Great little place with a huge range of beer from many, many different brewers. The staff were friendly, helpful and knowledgeable. Love the location, would be easy to throw back a couple of cold brews and soak in the ambience.

Stocked to the rafters with canned and bottled craft beer. On tap they have 6 options, the owner/bartender mentioned that they rotate regularly. We tried a jaw dropping strawberry I.P.A. which was subtle and crisp. Thumbs up x
Great beers from all around the world in an alfresco atmosphere that we would like to see more often in Hong Kong. Problem is too many french people around (including me)

reviews.text:
瓶や缶のクラフトビールを買う店だと思うけど、タップもあるし店の外にはそこそこ座れるところを用意してくれてて、酒屋の角打ちのオシャレ版みたいな感じかな。

瓶や缶のビールを買っても、外で飲みたいからプラコップくれる？と聞いたら笑顔でくれるのもありがたい。

香港島の坂を登って路地にあります。散歩の熱を冷ますのにちょうどよい風が通っていました。
